When I use scattergl with lines, none of the mobile browsers show the curve. Desktop works fine. Please use the following code to test on iPhone browsers (chrome, safari, edge, firefox, etc). Using scatter works fine.

<pre>

&lt;head&gt;
&lt;script type='text/javascript' src='https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.3.1/jquery.min.js'&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;script type='text/javascript' src='https://cdn.plot.ly/plotly-latest.min.js'&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;script&gt;

$( function() {

  TESTER = document.getElementById('myDiv');
  Plotly.newPlot( TESTER,
    [ {
        x: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],
        y: [1, 2, 4, 8, 16],
        mode: 'lines',
        type: 'scattergl',
      },
    ],
    { margin: { t: 0 } }
  );

} );

&lt;/script&gt;

&lt;/head&gt;

&lt;body&gt;
        &lt;div id='myDiv'&gt;&lt;!-- Plotly chart will be drawn inside this DIV --&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;

</pre>
